President Donald J. Trump, Vice President Mike Pence, and members of their Cabinet received a briefing on the ongoing response and recovery operations for Hurricane Irma. They also discussed Federal support for Hurricane Harvey recovery. President Trump emphasized the importance of life-saving and life-sustaining efforts in affected areas and praised the leadership provided by the Governors of affected States and territories, the Department of Homeland Security, and FEMA. He mentioned that he is in regular contact with Governors currently in the path of Hurricane Irma and extends his thoughts and prayers to those affected. He also acknowledged the efforts of volunteer and faith-based organizations in helping fellow Americans.